1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/your-username/rockybot-genai.git
cd rockybot-genai

2. Set up virtual environment (without Conda)
python -m venv venv
.\venv\Scripts\activate      # On Windows

3. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

4. Set your Google Gemini API key
GOOGLE_API_KEY=your-gemini-api-key

5. Run the app locally
streamlit run app.py


Deployment on Google Cloud Run (via Cloud Build)
‚úÖ Prerequisites
1.Python 3.10+
2.Google Cloud SDK installed and authenticated (gcloud auth login)
3.GCP project created (gen-ai-proj-460914)
4.Enable these services:

gcloud services enable run.googleapis.com cloudbuild.googleapis.com artifactregistry.googleapis.com

üîÅ Deployment Steps
1. Update Dockerfile
Make sure your Dockerfile uses this final version:
FROM python:3.10-slim
WORKDIR /app
COPY requirements.txt .
RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt
COPY . .
EXPOSE 8080
CMD streamlit run app.py --server.port=$PORT --server.address=0.0.0.0

2. Build & Push Docker Image to GCP
gcloud builds submit --config cloudbuild.yaml --project=gen-ai-proj-460914 .

3. Deploy to Cloud Run
gcloud run deploy rockybot-streamlit --image gcr.io/gen-ai-proj-460914/rockybot-streamlit --platform managed --region us-central1 --allow-unauthenticated --project=gen-ai-proj-460914 --update-env-vars GOOGLE_API_KEY="AIzaSyAF-r96MjMm1Bz-URtcxVna4dVnYAwFN6e"




